Citation.sTitle: Relative Permittivity, Viscosity, and Speed of Sound for 2-Methoxyethanol + Butylamine Mixtures
Citation.sAbstract: Relative permittivities at five temperatures, between (293.15 and 313.15) K, viscosities at three temperatures, between (293.15 and 303.15) K, and speeds of sound (u) at 298.15 K of binary mixtures of 2-methoxyethanol (1) + butylamine (2) are reported. From all those data, the deviations from mole fraction additivity of the relative permittivity, viscosity, and speed of sound (u) were calculated and fitted to a Redlich-Kister equation.
